      • at

        public Iterable<StorageInputStream> at(URI location,
                                       Object... args)
        Description copied from interface: StorageInterface
        Provides a means of iteration over all existing objects at a specified location, including those in sub-directories. This method is particularly nice for use in for-each loops. The provided scheme is not relevant at this point, but the developer must avoid calling this method with a path of a different schema. 
        for(StorageInputStream dicomObj : storagePlugin.at("file://dataset/")){
      System.err.println(dicomObj.getURI());
 }
        Specified by:
        at in interface StorageInterface
        Parameters:
        location - the location to read
        args - a variable list of extra parameters for the retrieve
        Returns:
        an iterable of storage input streams
        See Also:
        StorageInputStream

      • list

        public Stream<URI> list(URI location)
                 throws IOException
        Description copied from interface: StorageInterface
        Lists the elements at the given location in the storage's file tree. Unlike StorageInterface.at(java.net.URI, java.lang.Object...), this method is not recursive and can yield intermediate URIs representing other directories rather than objects. The provided scheme is not relevant at this point, but the developer must avoid calling this method with a path of a different scheme.
        Specified by:
        list in interface StorageInterface
        Parameters:
        location - the base storage location to list
        Returns:
        a standard stream of URIs representing entries in the given base location
        Throws:
        NoSuchFileException - if the given location does not exist in the storage
        NotDirectoryException - if the given location does not refer to a listable entry (a directory)
        IOException - if some other I/O error occurs
